reviewText: I was looking for an intense cardio workout - this wasn't it.  Very slow beginner moves - and stuff seemed repetitive.  I really wanted cardio, not weights - there was one cardio section and that was over the top.  She went from barely moving to full burpees and pushups.  I did enjoy that cardio part, but it wasn't enough.  I am not a beginner - my favorite cardio workout is the P90X Kenpo Plus workout.

reviewText: I consider myself at an intermediate level of fitness.Instructor manages to be high energy rather than annoying, although, unfortunately, her voice does get whiny/shrieky and having to hear the same conversations over and over on any DVD is a bad thing.  All DVDs should come with a music only option to solve this problem.Workout has decent music, non-annoying "backup dancers", and the moves are good with kickboxing form that is not painful to watch.  Overall, a good workout.

reviewText: This is a great workout program for people who enjoy some serious cardio without a lot of "fancy" moves or choreography. Jeanette does a great job describing the kicks and punches, doing many of them slow first before full speed, so in a few times through the program you're sure to get the hang of it. It doesn't get boring on repeat viewing, and you will definitely work up a good sweat! The routine is also set up with a few "breaks" for strength and weight training, so it's very balanced overall.Overall I definitely recommend the program. The only reason I give it 4 instead of 5 stars is the music isn't that great, and the camera work is sometimes a bit clumsy. But still, this is one I've certainly added to my regular workout video rotation!
